Cloud Club in the Chrysler Building closed, the one-time playroom
of Walter P. Chrysler and his fellow moguls has been ravaged by
time, neglect, water damage and vandalism. But the wide bronze and
marble staircase is still there. And the view through the arch of
the two-story high window still gazes south over the city. But
restaurateurs are not begging for the chance to breathe new life
into the Cloud Club. By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
