helicopter/turboprop, was scuttled by the Pentagon but Congress
kept it alive. Now three of the 15 finished military aircraft have
crashed, killing 26 soldiers, and the Pentagon has grounded the
remaining planes. The aircraft remains expensive, experimental and
exemplary of the way weapons are built for today's U.S. military.
By Tim Weiner.
