   BBA-YANKS-USHERS (New York) _ The hundreds of ushers that once
worked Yankee Stadium have steadily been replaced by beefy security
guards over the years. Now there are 8 ushers left, all in their
60s through 80s, and they will likely become extinct after this
season. Why? During negotiations, the Yankees claimed they could no
longer afford to pay the ushers their $72 a game salary because
they needed it for players salaries. By Corey Kilgannon.
