<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 16:02 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2437 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r d BC-BERRY-RECIPES-LADN &LR;      04-10 1477
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BERRY-RECIPES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: goes with Strawberries main, `A Match Made in Heaven') By NATALIE HAUGHTON 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHOCOLATE-STRAWBERRY PORT CAKE1/3 cup butter OR margarine &QL; 
1 cup (6 ounces) semisweet chocolate chips &QL; 
1/2 cup port wine &QL; 
2 eggs, separated &QL; 
1/2 cup sugar &QL; 
1/2 cup all-purpose flour &QL; 
1 pint basket (12 ounces) fresh strawberries, rinsed, stemmed and
sliced &QL; 
1 cup whipping cream, whipped and sweetened to taste
</P>
<P>
   Grease and flour a 9-inch-round layer cake pan. In a double
boiler over simmering water, melt butter with 1/2 cup chocolate
chips and 1/3 cup port; stir and cool.
</P>
<P>
   In a mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with 6 tablespoons sugar until
thick and pale. Gradually beat in chocolate mixture; mix in flour
and remaining 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
</P>
<P>
   In another bowl, beat egg whites with remaining 2 tablespoons
sugar just until stiff; gradually fold into chocolate batter to
blend. Pour into prepared pan.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in center of preheated 325-degree oven 25 to 30 minutes
until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5
minutes; loosen and invert onto plate.
</P>
<P>
   With back of spoon, press shallow indentation into center of
cake. Toss strawberries with remaining port; spoon into center of
cake. Pipe or spoon whipped cream around edge. Makes 6 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
STRAWBERRY-CHOCOLATE MOUSSE CAKE &QL; 
1 cup chocolate cookie OR chocolate graham cracker crumbs &QL; 
3 tablespoons butter OR margarine, melted &QL; 
2 pint baskets fresh strawberries, rinsed, stemmed and halved &QL; 
2 cups (12 ounces) semisweet chocolate chips &QL; 
1/2 cup water &QL; 
2 tablespoons light corn syrup &QL; 
2 1/2 cups whipping cream &QL; 
1 tablespoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, mix crumbs and butter to blend thoroughly. Press
evenly onto bottom of a 9-inch springform pan; set aside. Stand
strawberry halves, touching, side-by-side, pointed ends up with cut
sides against side of pan.
</P>
<P>
   Place chocolate chips in a blender container. In a small
saucepan over medium heat, mix water and corn syrup; bring to a
boil and simmer 1 minute. Immediately pour over chocolate chips and
blend until smooth. Cool to room temperature.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, in a large mixer bowl, beat 1 1/2 cups cream to form
stiff peaks. With a rubber spatula, fold cooled chocolate into
whipped cream to blend thoroughly. Pour into prepared pan; level
top. (Points of strawberries might extend above chocolate mixture.)
</P>
<P>
   Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours. Up to 2 hours before
serving, in a medium mixer bowl, beat remaining 1 cup cream to form
soft peaks. Add sugar; beat to form stiff peaks.
</P>
<P>
   Remove side of pan; place cake on a serving plate. Pipe or
dollop whipped cream onto top of cake. Arrange remaining halved
strawberries on whipped cream. To serve, cut into wedges with a
thin knife, wiping blade between cuts. Makes 12 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
STRAWBERRY-CHOCOLATE MOUSSE PARFAIT &QL; 
1 pint basket fresh strawberries, rinsed, stemmed and halved &QL; 
3 tablespoons orange-flavored liqueur OR 3 tablespoons frozen
orange juice concentrate, thawed &QL; 
3 tablespoons water &QL; 
2 1/2 tablespoons sugar &QL; 
1 cup (6 ounces) semisweet chocolate chips &QL; 
1 1/2 cups whipping cream &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon vanilla &QL; 
Mint sprigs for garnish
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, toss strawberries and liqueur; cover and refrigerate.
</P>
<P>
   To make chocolate mousse, in a small saucepan, mix water with 2
tablespoons sugar. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1
minute. Place chocolate chips in container of an electric blender.
Immediately add hot sugar mixture. Blend until chocolate is melted
and smooth.
</P>
<P>
   In a medium bowl, whip 3/4 cup cream to form stiff peaks. With
rubber spatula, fold cooled chocolate into cream to blend
thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours or
store up to 2 days.
</P>
<P>
   Just before serving, whip remaining 3/4 cup cream to form soft
peaks. Beat in remaining 1/2 tablespoon sugar and vanilla.
</P>
<P>
   In 10- to 12-ounce stemmed wine glasses or in dessert bowls,
layer mousse, whipped cream and strawberries, dividing equally.
Garnish with mint sprigs. Makes 4 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
STRAWBERRIES-HOT FUDGE SUNDAE CAKE &QL; 
1 cup flour &QL; 
2 teaspoons baking powder &QL; 
1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder &QL; 
1 cup granulated sugar &QL; 
3/4 cup milk &QL; 
1/2 cup butter OR margarine, melted &QL; 
1 teaspoon vanilla &QL; 
1/2 cup packed brown sugar &QL; 
1 cup water &QL; 
2 pint baskets fresh strawberries, rinsed and stemmed &QL; 
Vanilla OR coffee ice cream
</P>
<P>
   In a mixer bowl, combine flour, baking powder, 2 tablespoons
cocoa powder and 2/3 cup granulated sugar. Add milk, butter and
vanilla; beat until smooth and well blended. Spread in a greased
8-inch-square baking pan; set aside.
</P>
<P>
   In a small saucepan, combine remaining 1/3 cup granulated sugar,
remaining 6 tablespoons cocoa powder, brown sugar and water. Bring
to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar. Gently spoon over cake
batter.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven about 35 minutes, until
springy to touch.
</P>
<P>
   While cake is baking, slice strawberries into a bowl and toss
additional sugar to sweeten, if desired. To serve, spoon warm cake
and its sauce into individual bowls with scoops of ice cream and
sweetened strawberries. Makes 6 servings.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: Cake can be prepared ahead and served cooled or reheated
in a low oven. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
CHOCOLATE-DIPPED STRAWBERRIES &QL; 
2 pint baskets fresh strawberries &QL; 
1/2 cup EACH semisweet, milk and white chocolate chips &QL; 
Finely chopped toasted almonds OR pistachios (optional)
</P>
<P>
   Line a large baking sheet with waxed paper. Rinse strawberries
and pat dry with paper towels. In separate small, microwave-safe
bowls (such as custard cups), melt chocolates, one at a time, in a
microwave oven at 50 percent (medium) power, allowing 1 1/2 to 2
minutes for each. Stir until smooth. (If not completely melted,
microwave a few seconds longer.)
</P>
<P>
   Holding strawberry by stem end, dip into chocolate to cover
about 3/4 of berry; dip into nuts, if desired, and place on baking
sheet. Repeat with remaining strawberries, chocolates and nuts.
Refrigerate until chocolate is set. Makes about 8 servings (3
strawberries per serving.).
</P>
<P>
   FOR DOUBLE- AND TRIPLE-DIPPED STRAWBERRIES: After first coating
of chocolate is set, dip into contrasting chocolate, leaving part
of the first chocolate exposed. Repeat with third chocolate, if
desired, allowing each layer to set between dips.
</P>
<P>
   TO DRIZZLE STRAWBERRIES WITH CHOCOLATE: Microwave chocolate in a
small plastic food bag until melted; squeeze into one corner of
bag. Lay strawberries close together on baking sheet. With
scissors, cut a small hole in corner of bag and move back and forth
over strawberries, squeezing bag gently. Or drizzle contrasting
chocolate over strawberries that have been dipped. Refrigerate
until set. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
STRAWBERRY COOKIE PIE &QL; 
Chocolate Crumb Crust &QL; 
2 envelopes unflavored gelatin &QL; 
1/2 cup cold water &QL; 
2 pint baskets fresh strawberries, rinsed and stemmed &QL; 
1 1/2 tablespoons lemon juice &QL; 
2/3 cup sugar &QL; 
1 cup whipping cream &QL; 
Additional strawberries for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust; set aside.
</P>
<P>
   In a small saucepan, soften gelatin in cold water, about 3
minutes. Meanwhile, in a container of blender or food processor,
puree 2 baskets strawberries until slightly chunky. Transfer to a
large bowl; stir in lemon juice.
</P>
<P>
   Add sugar to gelatin mixture; stir over medium heat until
gelatin dissolves and mixture is clear. Do not boil. Remove from
heat and cool 5 minutes; mix into pureed strawberries. Chill,
stirring occasionally, until mixture is thickened but not
completely set.
</P>
<P>
   Beat cream to form soft peaks. Beat strawberry mixture just
until slightly foamy. With rubber spatula, fold strawberry mixture
into whipped cream until white streaks disappear. Mound into
prepared pie shell. Garnish with additional strawberries. Chill
until set, about 2 hours or longer. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   CHOCOLATE CRUMB CRUST: Place 7 ounces chocolate cookie wafers in
container of blender or food processor; process to make crumbs (you
should have 1 1/2 cups). In a bowl, mix crumbs and 1/2 cup butter,
melted. Press firmly onto bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 10 minutes. Cool. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
STRAWBERRY-CHOCOLATE GERMAN PANCAKE &QL; 
1/4 cup butter OR margarine &QL; 
4 eggs &QL; 
1 cup milk &QL; 
1 cup flour &QL; 
1 cup (6 ounces) semisweet chocolate chips &QL; 
1 pint basket fresh strawberries, rinsed, stemmed and sliced &QL; 
Powdered sugar
</P>
<P>
   Melt butter in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet. In container of an
electric blender, combine eggs, milk and flour; blend until smooth.
Pour into hot skillet.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 425-degree oven 2 minutes. Remove from oven;
sprinkle chocolate pieces over pancake and return to oven. Bake 15
to 20 minutes longer or until puffed and golden brown. Top with
strawberries and dust with powdered sugar. Serve immediately, cut
into wedges. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
</P>
</TEXT>
