<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY (Miami) _ The Florida relatives of Elian Gonzalez are
to meet with psychiatrists to work out a plan for returning the
6-year-old boy to his father, who arrived from Cuba last week and
is waiting to take custody of his son. By ARMANDO VILLAFRANCA.
</P>
<P>
   JOURNALIST-SLAIN (Harlingen, Texas) _ Mexican journalist Pablo
Pineda made a name for himself at La Opinion in Matamoros as a
crusader against corruption, which made him as unpopular with the
police as with criminals. Which is why it be difficult to identify
who killed him and then dumped his body on the U.S. side of the Rio
Grande Sunday. By JAMES PINKERTON.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-GAYS (Washington) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush's planned
meeting Thursday with gay Republicans is designed to show him as a
``compassionate conservative.'' But the session in Austin is
stirring great controversy within the gay community. By STEWART M.
POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINE-RATINGS (Washington) _ Southwest Airlines provided the
best service among the 10 major domestic airlines last year,
according to a report by university researchers. But despite the
industry's promise to improve service with a voluntary
customers-rights plan, passenger complaints jumped 130 percent. We
look at how the 10 airlines were ranked and at speculation that the
government may be asked again to set rules for better service. By
AUSTIN ZALKIN.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The only mystery left about the
Democratic and Republican presidential tickets is the identity of
the running mates. So naturally the game of `who?' is in full
swing. Will the nominees go for a bold choice or one that's merely
comfortable? This columnist hopes they both prefer an exciting one
to shake things up. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
