<P>
   COMPUTERS-GIRLS _ WASHINGTON _ Girls will continue to trail boys
in computer-related activities until there are changes in dull
computer courses and violent computer games, more tech-savvy
teachers and a change in the stereotype that computer pros ``live
in a solitary, antisocial and sedentary world.'' That's the
