<P>
   COKE-BIAS _ ATLANTA _ Following developments in the racial
discrimination case against Coca-Cola. (Unger, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   HOMEDEPOT-MAYTAG _ Home Depot will start carrying Maytag
appliances next month in selected markets to fill the gap left by
Whirlpool. Analysts have been waiting for Maytag, the No. 3
appliance maker, to step in after Home Depot dropped Whirlpool from
its appliance launch earlier this year. This could be a big boost
to Maytag. Whirlpool's stock plummeted when its delivery problems
to Home Depot were publicized. (Bond, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   CHARTER _ATLANTA _ The expected buyer of Charter Behavioral's 37
hospitals has backed out, but the Alpharetta-based company,
currently under bankruptcy protection, says that other companies
are interested in pieces or all of its psychiatric hospital
network. (Miller, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINE-QUALITY _ WASHINGTON _ University researches release the
the 10th annual National Airline Quality Rating. (Malone, Cox News
Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINE-DATA _ Chart material.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTERS-GIRLS _ WASHINGTON _ Girls will continue to trail boys
in computer-related activities until there are changes in dull
computer courses and violent computer games, more tech-savvy
teachers and a change in the stereotype that computer pros ``live
in a solitary, antisocial and sedentary world.'' That's the
conclusion of a report released for Tuesday papers by a national
commission appointed by the American Association of University
Women. (Mollison, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
