</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-THRASHERS-RECAP _ ATLANTA _ Thrashers recap of first season
and a look to hopefully better things next season. (Schultz,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/NFL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DRAFT-SIMON _ Florida State defensive tackle Corey Simon has
taken a different path than most draft prospects _ he signed with
Georgia out of high school, but transferred to FSU before he ever
stepped foot in Athens. In Tallahassee, he battled several injuries
throughout his career. His hard work paid off _ he's projected as a
top-5 pick (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DRAFT-FALCONS _ Dan Reeves has long believed in the
philosophy of drafting the best available athlete in NFL drafts.
But that won't happen this year. The Falcons will not select until
the second round, and there are too many glaring holes -- wide
receiver, secondary, offensive line -- to look elsewhere. It could,
and should be, a very strange draft for the Falcons. (Winkeljohn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-DOYLE _ Profiling defending champ of PGA Seniors'
Championship. (Dolch, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   SOC-PRO-TEAM _ ATLANTA _ The Women's United Soccer Association
said today that Atlanta will be one of eight teams in its new
league beginning next April. The eight initial markets are
conditional, pending completion of stadium contracts by Nov. 1.
(Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
