<HEADLINE>
TIMES PROMOTES DESIGN DIRECTOR, TOM BODKIN 
</HEADLINE>
  (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients. Nonsubscribers
can purchase one-time rights by calling 888-603-1036 or
888-346-9867.) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The appointment of Tom Bodkin as an assistant
managing editor of The New York Times was announced Monday by
Joseph Lelyveld, the executive editor.
</P>
<P>
   Bodkin, 47, was formerly an associate managing editor. He
retains the additional title of design director, heading the
paper's art department, including the information graphics and news
design staffs.
</P>
<P>
   After attending Brown University and working as a designer at
CBS, Bodkin joined The Times in 1980. He has designed or redesigned
many of the newspaper's sections and has received numerous awards,
including gold medals from the Society for News Design and the New
York Art Directors Club.
</P>
