<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 UPDATE &HT;    UPDATE
 &HT;    The Cox News Service spot news budget for Tuesday, April 11,
2000.
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Eds. Adds: USHER-HERO?, TEEN-ABUSE, CUBA-BUS
</P>
<P>
   Photo and graphics information and editors' names can be found
at the end of this budget.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   CUBA-ELIAN _ MIAMI _ As the saga of 6-year-old Elian Gonzalez
appears to be either winding down or coming to to a head, the
little boy's Miami family is expected to meet with
government-appointed child psychologists about how best to transfer
Elian to his father's custody. The Miami family, their backs
clearly to the wall with Attorney General Janet Reno remaining
steadfast in her insistence that they turn over the boy, are
expected to appeal to Florida state family court for relief from
federal pressure. The Miami exile community, meanwhile, continues
its vigil outside the family's Little Havana home to prevent Elian
being taken by federal immigration officials. Developing.
(Williams, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
