   EDs: Expected to move by 6 p.m. EST in (i) International and (w)
Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   w/CUBA-BUS _ WEST PALM BEACH _One to two busloads of Cuban
Americans from Palm Beach County are leaving at 5:30 p.m. from the
Cuba-American Club to visit Elian's house in Miami. They say they
want to show their support for his Miami relatives and their
efforts to keep the 6-year-old here. (Douthat, Palm Beach Post)
Moving by 10 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-BARAK _ WASHINGTON _ Advancing the Tuesday meeting here
between President Clinton and Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak,
with an eye toward
</P>
<P>
   putting the Middle East peace process on a faster track.
Developing. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 6 p.m. EST in both
International/Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINE-QUALITY _ WASHINGTON _ Despite promises of improved
service, airline service grew worse in nearly every category and
passenger complaints continued to grow, according to an annual
study of airline quality. (Turay, Cox News Service). 25.
