<SLUG> BC-DISCOBOXES11-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Classics back as remixed tunes
 &HT;    By Chris Hutchins
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The disco beat hasn't stopped, it's just
been turned around. DJs from all around the world are remixing
those hits of yesteryear into high-tech _ but equally danceable _
tunes.
</P>
<P>
   According to Oscar Zayas, a studio engineer at the Lake Worth
record shop Dancetarium, these five disco classics are the ones DJs
remix the most:
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Ring My Bell,'' by Anita Ward
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Disco Inferno,'' by the Trammps
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I Feel Love,'' by Donna Summer
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Let No Man Put Asunder,'' by Loleatta Holloway
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Stayin' Alive,'' by the Bee Gees
</P>
<P>
   WANT TO RECONNECT WITH DISCO? TRY WEB SITES
</P>
<P>
   Wanna relive the Disco Era _ or learn more about it? Sit down,
log on and check out these Web sites:
</P>
<P>
   _ The Disco Lounge: A good fun and frivolous place to start.
Here, you'll find photos, links and a page called ``Living the
Dream,'' where folks can submit their Disco stories from
yesteryear. www.geocities.com/SunsetStrip/Palladium/9002/index.html
</P>
<P>
   _ Discomusic.com: Includes a helpful ``Disco 101'' page for
newbies, a list of new disco compilation albums, and a ``vault''
featuring vintage album covers with mini-reviews.
www.discomusic.com/
</P>
<P>
   _ Disco Inferno: This place has information on '70s DJs,
interviews and histories of clubs long gone, like Studio 54.
hem.passagen.se/discoguy/
</P>
<P>
   _ DISCOnnected: Interesting Brazilian site with small bios on
many Disco artists. Also features information on the Brazilian
disco scene. www.geocities.com/SunsetStrip/Palms/9855/Main.html
</P>
<P>
   _ Heavy Vibes: A well-documented site about the disco era, its
performers, its music.
www.geocities.com/HotSprings/1392/HeavyVibes.html
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
