left-center field, huge stainless steel statues of Hall of Fame
players like Hank Greenberg, Ty Cobb and Charlie Gehringer will
keep watch. And the 10-story-tall scoreboard is the largest in
baseball, the Tiger organization says.
</P>
<P>
   As it is with most things, Comerica Park's grandeur comes at a
price. Now that the team offers luxury seats, the price of an
average home game ticket has doubled to $24.83, the fourth highest
in baseball, according to Team Marketing Report.
</P>
<P>
   But even that has done little to spoil this city's excitement.
</P>
<P>
   ``Detroit has lost so much and had to wait so long for something
to be proud of,'' said 63-year-old Bernard Battistelli, a longtime
Tiger fan, who typically attends 10 to 15 home games a year. ``I'd
rather pay a little extra than sit around another 10 years waiting
for a rebirth.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
