<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Tuesday, April 11, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Bob Schenet on the national-foreign desk at (206)
448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-BAE (Seattle) _ The Boeing Co. and BAE Systems, formerly
known as British Aerospace, will continue to court each other as
they look for joint business opportunities, but analysts say they
are not headed to the alter anytime soon.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Los Angeles) _ Seattle SuperSonics take on the
Lakers in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ On Ken Griffey Jr. and his 400th
home run..
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-TALK (Undated) _ There is no good reason for ``Talk to Me,''
an ABC series premiering Tuesday night, to be on the air. Period.
It is not funny. It is not imaginative. And, as comedy sets go, it
is not even all that pleasant to look at. Kyra Sedgwick, apparently
a graduate of the Trying Too Hard School of Comedy, is the star of
this dud. She also is one of five executive producers, which may
help explain why it's such a mess.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
